Uses of Interface
dagger.Lazy

  • Packages that use Lazy 
    Package Description
    dagger.internal  

    • Uses of Lazy in dagger.internal

      Classes in dagger.internal that implement Lazy 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  DoubleCheck<T>
      A Lazy and Provider implementation that memoizes the value returned from a delegate using the double-check idiom described in Item 71 of Effective Java 2.
      class  SingleCheck<T>
      A Provider implementation that memoizes the result of a Factory instance using simple lazy initialization, not the double-checked lock pattern.
      Methods in dagger.internal that return Lazy 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Lazy<T> ProviderOfLazy.get()
      Returns a new instance of Lazy<T>, which calls Provider.get() at most once on the Provider held by this object.
      static <T> Lazy<T> DoubleCheck.lazy(javax.inject.Provider<T> provider)
      Returns a Lazy that caches the value from the given provider.
      Methods in dagger.internal that return types with arguments of type Lazy 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static <T> javax.inject.Provider<Lazy<T>> ProviderOfLazy.create(javax.inject.Provider<T> provider)
      Creates a new Provider<Lazy<T>> that decorates the given Provider.
